<component type="desktop-application">
  <id>com.github.alexanderlanganke.ocrmypdfgui</id>
  
  <name>OCRmyPDF GUI</name>
  <summary>A graphical user interface for OCRmyPDF</summary>
  
  <metadata_license>MIT</metadata_license>
  <project_license>MIT</project_license>
  <developer_name>Alexander Langanke</developer_name>
  
  <description>
    <p>
      OCRmyPDF GUI provides a user-friendly graphical interface for the powerful OCRmyPDF command-line tool created by James R. Barlow. 
      This application allows users to easily apply Optical Character Recognition (OCR) to PDF files, making them searchable and accessible.
    </p>
    <p>
      As a hobby project, it aims to simplify the OCR process, especially for users who prefer a visual approach over command-line operations. 
      It supports batch processing, enabling users to process multiple PDF files at once.
    </p>
  </description>
  
